Best-selling author Jack Canfield believes that you can do anything. Having seen amputees play winning baseball and wrestle at the varsity level, he says that the biggest hindrance to success is the words "I can't". If, instead, you set concrete goals and deadlines, and regularly visualize success, your mind will find ways around obstacles. In this live presentation, Canfield shows you:

* How what you think makes you weak or strong

* Seven key areas of personal vision

* Two simple questions that unleash the power of goal-setting

* The Rule of Five for achieving your "breakthrough" goal
